ACA’s M&A Due Diligence service provides a comprehensive, off-site assessment of a target company’s IT, cybersecurity, and privacy posture. Designed for the pace and precision of today’s deal environment, our process equips deal teams with actionable insights, quantifiable risk data, and estimated remediation costs—all delivered within accelerated timelines.

Each engagement is led by ACA’s dedicated portfolio company practice and performed by experienced specialists across IT, cybersecurity, and privacy. The result is a concise yet robust evaluation of the target’s technology environment, operational resilience, and regulatory alignment—giving firms the clarity to move decisively through the transaction lifecycle.
